Crimean-Congo hem. fever - Russia (Dagestan) 20000703.1101
Date: Tue 17 Jul 2001 11:11:50 -0400
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Pravda (English edition online), 14 Jul 2001 [edited
<http://english.pravda.ru/society/2001/07/14/10071.html>

Outbreak of Crimean-Congo Haemorrhagic Fever in Dagestan
--------------------------------------------------------
Since the beginning of the year, 10 cases of Crimean-Congo haemorrhagic
fever have been registered in Dagestan, North Caucasus. All patients
survived, reports the Republican Sanitary and Epidemic Inspection.
This serious disease is carried by ticks. A total of 684 instances of
[ticks biting humans have been reported this year; 71 of these cases were
admitted to hospital as a precautionary measure.
